DAY-13

Aaj ka kaam (YouTube API Integration - Phase 3: Controller & API Endpoints)

1) YouTubeController Implementation
- Complete REST controller banaya with clean endpoints:
  - GET /api/youtube/search?query=java&max=5 → keyword-based video search
  - GET /api/youtube/popular?max=8 → popular programming videos
  - GET /api/youtube/topic/{topic}?max=6 → topic-specific curated videos
  - GET /api/youtube/health → API health check aur connectivity test

2) Frontend-Ready API Responses
- Proper JSON response structure with error handling:
  - Success responses with video arrays
  - Error responses with meaningful messages
  - CORS enabled for frontend integration (@CrossOrigin annotation)
  - ResponseEntity wrapper for proper HTTP status codes

3) YouTube API Error Handling
- Comprehensive error management:
  - API quota exceeded handling
  - Network connectivity issues management
  - Invalid API key detection aur user-friendly messages
  - Graceful degradation when YouTube service unavailable

4) Real-Time Video Data Integration
- Live YouTube data fetching:
  - Real video thumbnails, titles, descriptions
  - Actual view counts aur publish dates
  - Channel information aur video URLs
  - Duration data in user-friendly format

5) API Testing & Validation
- Postman-ready endpoints with proper documentation:
  - Query parameter validation
  - Max results limiting (default values)
  - Search term sanitization for better results

6) Health Check Endpoint
- /api/youtube/health endpoint features:
  - Simple connectivity test with YouTube API
  - Service status reporting
  - API key validation check
  - Response time monitoring

Testing Done
- All YouTube endpoints working with real API calls.
- Search functionality returning relevant educational videos.
- Health check confirming API connectivity.
- Error handling working for various failure scenarios.

Next Steps (DAY-14)
- Final testing aur bug fixes.
- Documentation completion.
- Production readiness checks.
- Complete project integration testing.

